{"parse":{"title":"Deadmines","pageid":293534,"redirects":[{"from":"The Deadmines","to":"Deadmines"}],"wikitext":{"*":"{{for|the pre-Cataclysm instance and associated lore|Deadmines (original)}} \n{{infobox instance\n|name=The Deadmines\n|aka=VC, DM, DMVC\n|ss=The Deadmines loading screen.jpg\n|caption=The Deadmines loading graphic\n|loc=[[Moonbrook]], [[Westfall]]\n|race={{Race|Goblin}}<br /> {{Race|Human}}<br /> {{Race|Murloc}}<br /> {{Race|Ogre}}<br /> {{Race|Worgen}}\n|boss=[[\"Captain\" Cookie]] (normal)<br>[[Vanessa VanCleef (tactics)|Vanessa VanCleef]] (heroic)\n|type=Dungeon\n|level=15 - 21 (85 [[Heroic mode|Heroic]])\n|minlevel=10\n|players=5\n|bosses={{Deadmines}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Deadmines''' are expansive, winding tunnels dug out under [[Westfall]] and part of [[Northern Stranglethorn]]. There is even a secret tunnel into [[Stormwind]]. It is the lowest level [[Alliance]] [[instance]], and is populated by members of the [[Defias Brotherhood]]. Its entrance can be accessed in the town of [[Moonbrook]] in southwestern [[Westfall]], while its exit is located in the western part of the [[Dagger Hills]] near the ocean.\n\nThe Deadmines once were the center of the Defias operation, led by the ambitious [[Edwin VanCleef]], who was constructing a [[juggernaut]] at the bottom of the mines with the aid of the [[goblin]]s. His plans were stopped by the Alliance militia and Edwin himself was killed and beheaded. It wasn't the end of the Brotherhood, as his daughter, [[Vanessa VanCleef|Vanessa]] witnessed his death and several years after began to slowly rebuild the organization, waiting for a proper moment to strike back against the Kingdom of Stormwind.\n\nPrior to the [[First War]], the Deadmines were the greatest gold-production center in human lands.  However, they were abandoned during the First War.  During that time, [[Lothar|Lord Lothar]] ventured into the perilous Deadmines on a quest to obtain the [[Tome of Divinity]] but was captured by a band of ogres and held captive for 20 months.  He was ultimately rescued and successful in his mission.  It was also to the dungeons below the Deadmines to which [[Blackhand|Blackhand's]] daughter [[Griselda]] fled with the ogre [[Turok]].  Both were slain by an orcish raid.  At that time, many [[slime]]s inhabited the dungeons but have not been encountered lately.\n\n== In Cataclysm ==\n{{cata-section}}\nThe dungeon was updated to reflect current events. The instance gained a Heroic mode for level 85 players. There are [[Goblin Teleporter]]s scattered throughout the instance, usable only when the boss of the particular room they are located in is killed. Once unlocked, they can send players to either Ironclad Cove, the Mast Room, or the Foundry. The Goblin Transporter located at the beginning room with the quest givers only sends players further into the instance; it does not function as a destination point.\n\n== Geography ==\nLocation: Westfall. Entrance to the mine is in the southwestern barn in Moonbrook. Keep right without taking dead-ends and you\u2019ll reach it, eventually. {{ref web\n|url = http://lorehound.com/wow/cataclysm-dungeon-location-gallery/\n|title = Cataclysm Dungeon Location Gallery}}\n\n=== Maps ===\n<gallery>\nFile:WorldMap-TheDeadmines1.jpg\nFile:WorldMap-TheDeadmines2.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== Quest guide ==\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n! colspan=\"4\" |{{Alliance Icon Small}} Alliance quests\n|-\n! Quest name\n! colspan=\"2\" | Quest giver\n|-\n|{{questlong|Alliance|16|The Foreman}}||{{NPC||Lieutenant Horatio Laine}}\n|-\n|{{questlong|Alliance|16|The Carpenter}}||{{NPC||Lieutenant Horatio Laine}}<br />(Automatic)\n|-\n|{{questlong|Alliance|16|The Machination}}||{{NPC||Lieutenant Horatio Laine}}<br />(Automatic)\n|-\n|{{questlong|Alliance|16|The Admiral}}||{{NPC||Lieutenant Horatio Laine}}<br />(Automatic)\n|-\n|{{questlong|Alliance|17|The Defias Kingpin (Alliance)|The Defias Kingpin}}||{{NPC||Lieutenant Horatio Laine}}<br />(Automatic)\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" |{{Horde Icon Small}} Horde quests\n|-\n! Quest name\n! colspan=\"2\" | Quest giver\n|-\n|{{questlong|Horde|16|Not Quite There}}||{{NPC||Miss Mayhem}}\n|-\n|{{questlong|Horde|16|Traitors!!!}}||{{NPC||Slinky Sharpshiv}}\n|-\n|{{questlong|Horde|16|Only the Beginning}}||{{NPC||Kagtha}}\n|-\n|{{questlong|Horde|16|Good Intentions...Poor Execution}}||{{NPC||Kagtha}}<br />(Automatic)\n|-\n|{{questlong|Horde|17|The Defias Kingpin (Horde)|The Defias Kingpin}}||{{NPC||Kagtha}}<br />(Automatic)\n\n|}\n\n== Dungeon denizens ==\n* {{Race|Goblin}}s\n* {{RaceIconExt|HarvestGolem}} [[Harvest golem]]s\n* {{RaceIconExt|Hobgoblin}} [[Hobgoblin]]s\n* {{Race|Human}}s\n* {{RaceIconExt|Kobold}} [[Kobold]]s\n* {{RaceIconExt|Monkey}} [[Monkey]]s\n* {{RaceIconExt|Murloc}} [[Murloc]]s (one, [[\"Captain\" Cookie]])\n* {{RaceIcon|Ogre|Male}} [[Ogre]]s\n* {{RaceIconExt|Ogre Male2}} [[Ogre magi]] (one, [[Glubtok]])\n* {{RaceIconExt|Parrot}} [[Parrot]]s\n* {{RaceIconExt|Rat}} [[Rat]]s (Critters)\n* {{RaceIconExt|Steam}} [[Steam elemental]]s\n* {{RaceIcon|Worgen|Male}} [[Worgen]] (one, [[Admiral Ripsnarl]])\n\n=== Staging Area ===\n;{{Alliance}} Alliance\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Horatio Laine||Lieutenant Horatio Laine|icon=Human Male}}\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Quartermaster Lewis|Quartermaster|icon=Human Male}}\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Stormwind Defender|icon=Human Male}}\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Stormwind Investigator|icon=Human Male}}\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Crime Scene Alarm-o-Bot|icon=Alarm}}\n\n;{{Horde}} Horde\n*{{NPC|Horde|Miss Mayhem|icon=Goblin Female}}\n*{{NPC|Horde|Kagtha|icon=Orc Female}}\n*{{NPC|Horde|Slinky Sharpshiv|icon=Goblin Female}}\n*{{NPC|Horde|Shattered Hand Assassin (Deadmines)||Shattered Hand Assassin|icon=Orc Male}}\n*{{NPC|Horde|Mayhem Reaper Prototype|icon=HarvestGolem}}\n*{{NPC|Horde|Vend-O-Tron D-Luxe|icon=TrainaTron}}\n\n=== Encounters ===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Rares || NPCs/Mobs\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|\n* '''Deadmines (Exterior)'''\n**{{NPC||Marisa du'Paige|icon=Human Female}}\n**{{NPC||Brainwashed Noble|icon=Human Male}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Homeless Stormwind Citizen}}\n* {{NPC||West Plains Drifter}}\n* {{NPC||Orphan}}\n* {{NPC||Small-time Hustler}}\n* {{NPC||Transient}}\n* {{NPC||Foreman Thistlenettle}}\n* {{NPC||Undead Excavator}}\n* {{NPC||Undead Dynamiter}}\n* {{NPC||Skeletal Miner}}\n|}\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Bosses || Monsters\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|\n* '''Deadmines (Entrance)'''\n**{{NPC||Glubtok|icon=Ogre Male2}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Kobold Digger (Deadmines)||Kobold Digger}}\n* {{NPC||Ogre Henchman}}\n* {{NPC||Ogre Bodyguard}}\n|- valign=\"top\" class=\"alt\"\n|\n* '''Deadmines (Tunnel to Mast Room)'''\n|\n* {{NPC||Mining Monkey}}\n* {{NPC||Goblin Overseer}}\n* {{NPC||Mine Bunny}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|\n* '''Mast Room'''\n**{{NPC||Helix Gearbreaker|icon=Goblin Male}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Oaf Lackey}}\n* {{NPC||Lumbering Oaf}}\n|- valign=\"top\" class=\"alt\"\n|\n* '''Deadmines (Tunnel to Foundry)'''\n|\n* {{NPC||Defias Digger}}\n* {{NPC||Defias Envoker}}\n* {{NPC||Defias Miner}}\n* {{NPC||Defias Overseer}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|\n* '''Goblin Foundry'''\n**{{NPC||Foe Reaper 5000|icon=HarvestGolem}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Defias Reaper}}\n* {{NPC||Defias Watcher}}\n|- valign=\"top\" class=\"alt\"\n|\n* '''Deadmines (Tunnel to Cove)'''\n|\n* {{NPC||Defias Blood Wizard}}\n* {{NPC||Defias Enforcer}}\n* {{NPC||Defias Shadowguard}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|\n* '''Ironclad Cove'''\n**{{NPC||Admiral Ripsnarl|icon=Worgen Male}}\n**{{NPC||\"Captain\" Cookie|icon=Murloc}}\n**{{NPC||Vanessa VanCleef (tactics)||Vanessa VanCleef|icon=Vanessa}} (Heroic mode)\n|\n* {{NPC||Brilliant Macaw}}\n* {{NPC||Monstrous Parrot}}\n* {{NPC||Sunwing Squawker}}\n* {{NPC||Ol' Beaky}}\n* {{NPC||Defias Pirate}}\n* {{NPC||Defias Squallshaper}}\n|}\n\n== Loot ==\nSee [[Deadmines loot|The Deadmines loot]].\n\n== Media ==\n=== Gallery ===\n<gallery>\nMast Room.jpg|Mast Room\nGoblin Foundry.jpg|Goblin Foundry\nIronclad Cove.jpg|Ironclad Cove\nDeadmines Inside.jpg|Within the Deadmines\n</gallery>\n=== Videos ===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|- valign=\"top\"\n! colspan=\"2\" | Various walkthroughs/guides\n|-\n! width=\"50%\" | Full Dungeon Guide (Normal) !! Normal/Heroic Guide by [http://love2playwow.com/ love2playwow.com]\n|-\n! [[File:Gnomeschool The Deadmines (WoW Dungeon Guide and Lore)|320px]]\n! [[File:Deadmines Dungeon Guide|320px]]\n|-\n! Entrance location !! {{Alliance Icon Small}} All Bosses Heroic: Paladin Tanking Perspective (1080p)\n|-\n! [[File:How to find your way into the Deadmines instance (normal and heroic)|320px]]\n! [[File:Paladin Tanking Heroic Deadmines Part 1 - World of Warcraft|320px]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|- valign=\"top\"\n! colspan=\"2\" | Various walkthroughs/guides\n|-\n! width=\"50%\" | !!\n|-\n! [[File:Deadmines Heroic - Dungeon Guide and Commentary|320px]]\n! [[File:LoD Deadmines Guide (Heroic Mode)|320px]]\n|-\n! !!\n|-\n! [[File:How To - Vigorous Vancleef Vindicator - Heroic Deadmines Nightmare Event|320px]]\n|}\n\n== Related achievements ==\n* {{achievementlong|Deadmines (achievement)}}\n** {{achievementlong|Heroic: Deadmines}}\n* {{achievementlong|Deadmines Guild Run}}\n** {{achievementlong|Heroic: Deadmines Guild Run}}\n* {{achievementlong|I'm on a Diet}}\n* {{achievementlong|It's Frost Damage}}\n* {{achievementlong|Prototype Prodigy}}\n* {{achievementlong|Rat Pack}}\n* {{achievementlong|Ready for Raiding}}\n* {{achievementlong|Vigorous VanCleef Vindicator}}\n\n== Notes, Tips, & Additional Info ==\n[[File:The Deadmines Exit.jpg|thumb|Exit from Deadmines instance.]]\n[[File:DeadminesWaterGate.jpg|thumb|The water gate, visible from the cove near Yojamba Isle in Stranglethorn Vale.]]\n* Also known as VC (named for its final boss, VanCleef) to avoid confusion with another instance ([[Dire Maul]]) that shares the more obvious initials. When in doubt about \"which DM\" is meant, check the level of the person asking for a group; a lower level character is most likely referring to this instance and is unaware of Dire Maul, or of the use of \"VC\" as an abbreviation.\n* If you travel to a small cove north of [[Yojamba Isle]] (in northwestern [[Northern Stranglethorn]]), you can see a large water gate which leads to the docks inside Deadmines. However, you cannot enter or leave through this. Interestingly, inside the Deadmines this gate exists to the North, but outside the gates exit to the south.\n*Very popular [http://www.wow.com/2010/03/17/wow-moviewatch-welcome-to-the-deadmines/ video] which won the Rise to Power contest was based on The Deadmines and its (old) bosses.\n*The Mining Monkeys start yellow (neutral) but if you release their ball and chain, they turn green and will attack your enemies.\n*There is a secret area underneath the dungeon that could be accessed by a mage blinking through the Dungeon portal entrance and using slow fall. This is now no longer possible due to an invisible wall that has been placed there by Blizzard. The area has a similar resemblance to Nagrand and some people believe it was a testing area for The Burning Crusade Expansion. There are rumours the area still exists after the dungeon was revamped in Cataclysm, but is no longer reachable.\n\n== Patches and hotfixes ==\n* {{Patch 4.0.3|note=Completely revamped, gained a heroic mode for level 85 players.}}\n* {{Patch 1.5.0|note=New load screen added.}}\n* {{Patch 1.3.0|note=\n**Capped at ten players.\n**The \"cannon door\" can now be opened with a Small Seaforium Charge in addition to the lockpick ability.}}\n\n== References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Read http://www.wowwiki.com/WoWWiki:External_links before posting your links here.\nLinks that do not conform to the rules will be DELETED.\nRepeat violations may result in a BAN.\nHave a nice day. :) -->\n{{Bnetwowinstance|{{PAGENAME}}}}\n{{elinks-zone|1581}}\n\n\n{{Deadmines Subzones}}\n{{Dungeons}}\n\n[[de:Todesminen]]\n[[fr:Les Mortemines]]\n[[ru:\u041c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043f\u0438]]\n[[Category:The Deadmines| ]]\n[[Category:Westfall]]\n[[Category:Mines]]\n[[Category:Instances]]"}}}